# Section spacing (required for new sections)

When **creating a new** `sections/*.liquid` file, include Theme Editor controls for **padding**, **margin**, and **column gap** (when applicable) at **three breakpoints**.

## Breakpoints

| Breakpoint | Viewport | Media query |
|------------|----------|-------------|
| Desktop | 1024px and up | Default (base styles) |
| Tablet | 768pxâ€“1023px | `@media screen and (min-width: 768px) and (max-width: 1023px)` |
| Mobile | 767px and below | `@media screen and (max-width: 767px)` |

## Setting IDs

**Desktop** â€” no suffix: `padding_top`, `padding_bottom`, `padding_left`, `padding_right`, `margin_top`, `margin_bottom`, `margin_left`, `margin_right`.

**Tablet** â€” `_tablet` suffix: `padding_top_tablet`, `margin_left_tablet`, etc.

**Mobile** â€” `_mobile` suffix: `padding_top_mobile`, `margin_left_mobile`, etc.

**Multi-column layouts** (grid/flex with 2+ columns): `column_gap`, `column_gap_tablet`, `column_gap_mobile`.

Schema: group under headers â€” `Section padding â€” Desktop`, `Section padding â€” Tablet`, `Section padding â€” Mobile`, same for margin; `Column spacing` for gap fields.

Range fields: padding/margin `min: 0`, `max: 120`, `step: 4`, `unit: px`, `default: 0`. Column gap `min: 0`, `max: 96`, `step: 4` or `8`, `default: 0` or a sensible layout default (e.g. 48 desktop).

Info text: `0 = theme default` for top/bottom padding (use `section-spacing` class); `0 = theme horizontal padding` for left/right (`var(--section-padding-x, 40px)`); margin `0 = none`.

## Markup & CSS

1. Root element: `<section class="my-section section-spacing">` (or inner `__inner` wrapper) with BEM class.
2. Scoped `<style>`: `#shopify-section-{{ section.id }}`.
3. Apply padding/margin only when value `> 0` (per side, per breakpoint).
4. Desktop rules first (no media), then tablet block, then mobile block.
5. Column gap: set `gap` (or `column-gap` / `row-gap`) on the multi-column container; use breakpoint-specific settings, not a single hardcoded gap when columns exist side by side.

```liquid
{%- if section.settings.padding_top > 0 -%}
  #shopify-section-{{ section.id }} .my-section {
    padding-top: {{ section.settings.padding_top }}px;
  }
{%- endif -%}
@media screen and (min-width: 768px) and (max-width: 1023px) {
  {%- if section.settings.padding_top_tablet > 0 -%}
    #shopify-section-{{ section.id }} .my-section {
      padding-top: {{ section.settings.padding_top_tablet }}px;
    }
  {%- endif -%}
}
@media screen and (max-width: 767px) {
  {%- if section.settings.padding_top_mobile > 0 -%}
    #shopify-section-{{ section.id }} .my-section {
      padding-top: {{ section.settings.padding_top_mobile }}px;
    }
  {%- endif -%}
}
```

When tablet/mobile padding is `0`, inherit desktop/theme (do not zero out unless intentional).

## Multi-column

Required when the section has **two or more columns** on any breakpoint (e.g. content + image, card grid columns). Apply `column_gap` / `column_gap_tablet` / `column_gap_mobile` to the grid/flex wrapper. If columns **stack** on tablet/mobile, gap still controls vertical spacing between stacked items.

## Checklist before done

- [ ] 12 padding settings (4 sides Ă— 3 breakpoints)
- [ ] 12 margin settings (4 sides Ă— 3 breakpoints)
- [ ] `column_gap` trio if multi-column
- [ ] Styles scoped to `#shopify-section-{{ section.id }}`
- [ ] Schema labels in English
- [ ] See `snippets/spacing-settings-reference.liquid` for copy-paste templates

## Do not

- Ship new sections with only global `section-spacing` and no per-side/per-breakpoint controls
- Use one `column_gap` for all breakpoints when layout stacks differently
- Skip re-reading files (see `read-before-modify` rule)
